[2026-03-15T18:56:28Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MUQcEWdHV2GEJu3gAkcznX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the evolution system. Let me compile all the information into a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution System Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete guide to the evolution system, including the Curator, Audit/snapshot system, and prompt evolution:\n\n### Core Files and Directory Structure\n\n**Evolution Package Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` - Prompt curation and merging\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` - Audit logging and snapshot management\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` - Pipeline orchestration\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` - Core data structures\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` - Data collection from runs\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go` - Run classification (bug/feature/etc.)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` - Lesson extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` - Script/prompt file generation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go` - LLM invocation wrapper\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` - Debouncing and triggering logic\n\n**Ports Interface:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (contains EvolutionStore and EvolutionEntry)\n\n**Design Documents:**\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n\n---\n\n### Data Structures\n\n#### EvolutionResult\n```go\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   // \"evo-<timestamp>\"\n    ProjectDir     string   // Absolute path to project\n    WorkflowName   string   // Workflow name (e.g., \"develop\")\n    TriggerRunID   string   // Run that triggered evolution\n    Timestamp      string   // RFC3339 format\n    Classification string   // bug/feature/feedback/enhancement/chore\n    Changes        []Change // All modifications made\n    KnowledgeDelta string   // Description of knowledge base updates\n}\n```\n\n#### Change (Evolution Result Record)\n```go\ntype Change struct {\n    Type     string // \"prompt_update\", \"add_step\", \"add_script\"\n    File     string // Relative path to modified file\n    Reason   string // Lesson insight driving the change\n    Snapshot string // Snapshot filename for rollback\n}\n```\n\n#### Lesson (Extracted Knowledge)\n```go\ntype Lesson struct {\n    ID              string   // Unique ID for deduplication\n    Category        string   // \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n    StepType        string   // \"script\" or \"agent\" (for new_step)\n    Target          string   // Target file path (for prompt_improvement)\n    Insight         string   // What pattern was observed\n    SuggestedAction string   // Concrete change to make\n    Evidence        []string // Run IDs supporting the lesson\n    Confidence      string   // \"high\", \"medium\", or \"low\"\n}\n```\n\n#### EvolutionEntry (Database/Storage)\n```go\ntype EvolutionEntry struct {\n    ID             string\n    ProjectDir     string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    TriggerRunID   string\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    Classification string\n    ChangesJSON    string\n    KnowledgeDelta string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Algorithms and Methods\n\n#### 1. Curator.Apply() - Prompt Merging with ACE Principles\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go:32-87`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Reads the target prompt file from disk\n2. Checks if lesson is already present (case-insensitive substring match on insight/action)\n   - If present, returns nil (no change needed)\n3. Takes a snapshot BEFORE modification via `c.Audit.Snapshot()`\n4. Calls LLM with ACE-style system prompt to merge lesson into prompt\n   - System prompt instructs: append to \"## Learned Rules\" section, preserve existing content\n5. Strips markdown code fences from LLM response\n6. Validates response isn't conversational meta-text (checks for patterns like \"I need write permission\", \"Here is the updated\")\n   - If conversational, falls back to appending lesson directly\n7. Writes updated content to target file\n8. Returns Change record with snapshot reference\n\n**Snapshot Protection:** Happens BEFORE file write to capture pre-change state\n\n```go\n// Snapshot before writing\nvar snapName string\nif c.Audit != nil {\n    snapName, _ = c.Audit.Snapshot(lesson.Target)\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. AuditLogger.Snapshot() - Pre-Change File Backup\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:44-73`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Creates `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/` directory if needed\n2. Generates snapshot filename: `<timestamp>-<basename>` (e.g., `20260315T164200-implement.md`)\n3. Opens source file, creates destination in snapshots dir\n4. Copies file content using `io.Copy()`\n5. Returns snapshot filename for audit trail\n\n**Key Detail:** Called with relative paths (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`), constructs full path internally\n\n```go\nsnapName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", time.Now().Format(\"20060102T150405\"), basename)\ndstPath := filepath.Join(snapDir, snapName)\n```\n\n#### 3. AuditLogger.Log() - JSONL Audit Trail\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:19-42`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Creates `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` if needed\n2. Opens file in APPEND mode (preserves history)\n3. JSON-marshals EvolutionResult\n4. Appends line to JSONL file (one JSON object per line)\n\n```go\nf, err := os.OpenFile(logPath, os.O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY, 0644)\ndata, err := json.Marshal(result)\nf.Write(append(data, '\\n'))\n```\n\n#### 4. AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() - Knowledge Base Management\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:124-155`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Reads existing JSONL knowledge base (`.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl`)\n2. Builds index of lesson IDs\n3. For each new lesson:\n   - If ID exists: updates in place (replaces existing entry)\n   - If ID is new: appends to list\n4. If MaxPromptBullets set and exceeded:\n   - Keeps only the newest N lessons (prunes oldest)\n5. Writes merged lessons back to JSONL\n\n```go\n// Merge: update in place if ID exists, append if new\nfor _, l := range lessons {\n    if idx, ok := idIndex[l.ID]; ok {\n        existing[idx] = l // update existing entry\n    } else {\n        existing = append(existing, l)\n    }\n}\n\n// Prune oldest entries if MaxPromptBullets exceeded\nif a.MaxPromptBullets > 0 && len(existing) > a.MaxPromptBullets {\n    existing = existing[len(existing)-a.MaxPromptBullets:]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Pipeline Architecture\n\n**5-Stage Evolution Pipeline:**\n\n1. **Collector** - Gathers data:\n   - Runs since last evolution pass\n   - Knowledge base (JSONL format)\n   - Current prompt files (from `file()` references in workflow)\n   - Current workflow DSL content\n\n2. **Classifier** - Categorizes triggering run via LLM:\n   - Output: \"bug\" | \"feedback\" | \"feature\" | \"enhancement\" | \"chore\"\n   - Used to weight analysis\n\n3. **Reflector** - Extracts lessons via LLM:\n   - Input: collected runs, prompts, workflow, knowledge base\n   - Output: structured lessons with confidence levels\n   - Filters by MinConfidence (high/medium/low)\n   - Deduplicates against knowledge base IDs\n\n4. **Executor Branches** (based on lesson category):\n   - **prompt_improvement** → Curator.Apply()\n   - **new_step** → ScriptGenerator + DSL Mutator\n\n5. **Audit** - Records changes:\n   - Logs to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n   - Creates snapshots in `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   - Updates knowledge base with ID-based deduplication\n\n---\n\n### Snapshot System\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n.cloche/\n  evolution/\n    log.jsonl                     # Append-only JSONL audit trail\n    knowledge/\n      <workflow>.jsonl            # ID-keyed lessons\n    snapshots/\n      20260315T164200-implement.md\n      20260315T164215-develop.cloche\n      ...\n```\n\n**How Snapshots are Used:**\n\n1. **Before Curator writes prompt:**\n   ```go\n   snapName, _ := c.Audit.Snapshot(lesson.Target)  // Returns \"20260315T164200-implement.md\"\n   os.WriteFile(targetPath, []byte(updated), 0644) // Write updated content\n   return &Change{Snapshot: snapName}              // Track for rollback\n   ```\n\n2. **Before workflow file modification:**\n   ```go\n   wfRelPath, _ := filepath.Rel(o.cfg.ProjectDir, data.WorkflowPath)\n   snapName, _ := o.audit.Snapshot(wfRelPath)      // Snapshot before DSL mutation\n   os.WriteFile(data.WorkflowPath, []byte(updated), 0644)\n   ```\n\n3. **Future Rollback** (not yet implemented):\n   - Snapshots enable automated revert via `cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`\n\n---\n\n### Curator Details: Content Guards and Fallbacks\n\n**Guard 1: Lesson Already Present Check** (before LLM call)\n```go\nif lessonAlreadyPresent(string(current), lesson) {\n    return nil, nil  // No change needed\n}\n```\nCase-insensitive substring match on Insight or SuggestedAction.\n\n**Guard 2: Code Fence Stripping**\n```go\nupdated := stripCodeFences(raw)\n```\nExtracts content between ``` markers, removing LLM's commentary/markdown formatting.\n\n**Guard 3: Conversational Response Detection**\n```go\nif isConversationalResponse(updated) {\n    // Fallback: append lesson directly\n    updated = appendLessonDirectly(string(current), lesson)\n}\n```\n\nPatterns detected:\n- \"I need write permission\"\n- \"Could you grant access\"\n- \"Here is the updated prompt:\"\n- \"Let me update...\"\n- Permission-related messages\n- Blocked/access errors\n\nIf detected, fallback to deterministic appending instead of trusting LLM output.\n\n**Fallback Appending:**\n```go\n// If \"## Learned Rules\" section exists, append to it\n// Otherwise, create new section\nif strings.Contains(current, \"## Learned Rules\") {\n    return current + fmt.Sprintf(\"\\n- %s: %s\\n\", lesson.Insight, lesson.SuggestedAction)\n} else {\n    return current + fmt.Sprintf(\"\\n\\n## Learned Rules\\n\\n- %s: %s\\n\", lesson.Insight, lesson.SuggestedAction)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Orchestrator.Run() - Complete Pipeline Execution\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go:51-138`\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n1. Collector.Collect() → CollectedData\n2. Classifier.Classify() → classification string\n3. Reflector.Reflect() → []Lesson (with confidence filtering)\n4. Filter out lessons already in knowledge base (ID deduplication)\n5. Create EvolutionResult\n6. For each lesson:\n   - If category == \"prompt_improvement\":\n     - Call curator.Apply()\n     - Append Change to result\n   - If category == \"new_step\":\n     - Call scriptGen.Generate()\n     - Call mutator to add step/wiring\n     - Append Changes to result\n7. Audit:\n   - audit.UpdateKnowledge() (ID-based merge + prune)\n   - audit.Log(result) (append to JSONL)\n   - evoStore.SaveEvolution() (if available)\n8. Return EvolutionResult\n\n---\n\n### Knowledge Base System\n\n**Format:** JSONL (one JSON Lesson per line)\n\n**Deduplication Strategy:**\n1. Lessons keyed by ID field\n2. If same ID appears: update in place (not append)\n3. ReadKnowledge parses JSONL, builds ID index\n4. WriteKnowledge serializes back\n\n**Deduplication Layers:**\n1. **Orchestrator layer** (before Curator/ScriptGen):\n   ```go\n   if data.KnowledgeBase != \"\" {\n       var fresh []Lesson\n       for _, l := range lessons {\n           if l.ID != \"\" && strings.Contains(data.KnowledgeBase, l.ID) {\n               continue  // Skip already-seen ID\n           }\n           fresh = append(fresh, l)\n       }\n       lessons = fresh\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **AuditLogger layer** (UpdateKnowledge):\n   ```go\n   for _, l := range lessons {\n       if idx, ok := idIndex[l.ID]; ok {\n           existing[idx] = l  // Update in place\n       } else {\n           existing = append(existing, l)\n       }\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Pruning:**\n```go\nif a.MaxPromptBullets > 0 && len(existing) > a.MaxPromptBullets {\n    existing = existing[len(existing)-a.MaxPromptBullets:]  // Keep newest N\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration with Rest of System\n\n**Ports Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n```go\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Trigger System** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`):\n- Debounces evolution runs per project+workflow\n- Resets timer if new run completes within debounce window\n- Default: 30 seconds\n\n**LLM Client** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`):\n- Interface: `Complete(ctx, systemPrompt, userPrompt) (string, error)`\n- CommandLLMClient: invokes external command (e.g., Claude Code CLI)\n- Passes system prompt via `--system-prompt` flag\n- Uses `-p` (print mode) for non-interactive output\n\n---\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` (1198 lines)\n  - Collector tests\n  - Classifier tests\n  - Reflector tests\n  - Audit Logger tests (Log, Snapshot, UpdateKnowledge, deduplication, pruning)\n  - Curator tests (prompt update, code fence stripping, conversational response detection)\n  - ScriptGenerator tests\n  - Utility function tests\n\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go`\n  - Error handling and edge cases\n  - Mock stores for integration testing\n\n- `/workspace/test/integration/evolution_test.go`\n  - End-to-end pipeline test\n\n**Mock Implementations:**\n- `fakeLLM` - Returns fixed responses\n- `callTrackingLLM` - Records all LLM calls (system/user prompts)\n- `errLLM` - Returns errors\n- `mockEvolutionStore` - Tracks saves/queries\n- `mockCaptureStore` - Returns test captures\n\n---\n\n### File Structure on Disk\n\n**Evolution artifacts location:**\n```\n<project-root>/\n  .cloche/\n    evolution/\n      log.jsonl                      # Append-only audit trail\n      knowledge/\n        develop.jsonl               # Knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n        test.jsonl                  # Knowledge base for 'test' workflow\n      snapshots/\n        20260315T150405-implement.md\n        20260315T150420-develop.cloche\n        ...\n    develop.cloche                  # Workflow DSL (can be modified)\n    prompts/\n      implement.md                  # Prompt files (can be modified)\n      fix.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Principles\n\n1. **Snapshot-First**: Snapshots taken before ANY file write (Curator or Mutator)\n2. **Deduplication**: Multi-layer (Orchestrator + AuditLogger) prevents lesson re-processing\n3. **LLM Validation**: Multiple guards against LLM producing meta-conversation instead of content\n4. **Deterministic Fallback**: If LLM fails validation, append lesson directly without re-calling\n5. **Audit Trail**: Complete JSONL history of every evolution pass with reasons\n6. **Project Scoping**: All evolution state scoped by `project_dir + workflow_name`\n7. **ACE Principles**: Prompts treated as structured playbooks with accumulated lessons, not monoliths\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Key Method |\n|-----------|---|---|\n| **Curator** | Merge lessons into prompts | `Apply(ctx, projectDir, lesson)` → Change |\n| **AuditLogger** | Log changes + snapshots + knowledge | `Log()`, `Snapshot()`, `UpdateKnowledge()` |\n| **Orchestrator** | Wire all stages together | `Run(ctx, triggerRunID, stores)` → EvolutionResult |\n| **Collector** | Gather input data | `Collect(ctx, stores)` → CollectedData |\n| **Classifier** | Categorize run | `Classify(ctx, prompt)` → string |\n| **Reflector** | Extract lessons | `Reflect(ctx, data, classification)` → []Lesson |\n| **ScriptGenerator** | Generate validation scripts | `Generate(ctx, projectDir, lesson)` → GeneratedScript |\n| **Trigger** | Debounce pipeline runs | `Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)` |\n\n---\n\nAll source files are in `/workspace/internal/evolution/` and thoroughly tested in `evolution_test.go` and `corruption_test.go`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a28439baa190cc1c6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57807\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 95229</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"937aed02-7c16-4e6e-ac4e-ccdcceb237c8","uuid":"864ba498-f209-4c47-bd0a-800c3ee91cbb","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all files related to the evolution system, specifically the Curator, Audit/snapshot system, and prompt evolution. Search for:\n1. Files containing \"Curator\" or \"curator\" \n2. Files containing \"Audit\" or \"audit\" or \"snapshot\" in the evolution context\n3. Files related to prompt evolution\n4. The evolution package/directory structure\n\nBe very thorough - check internal/, pkg/, and any other directories. I need to understand:\n- How Curator.Apply() works\n- How snapshots are taken before writing\n- How the audit system works\n- The data structures for evolution results and Change entries","agentId":"a28439baa190cc1c6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the evolution system. Let me compile all the information into a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution System Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's a complete guide to the evolution system, including the Curator, Audit/snapshot system, and prompt evolution:\n\n### Core Files and Directory Structure\n\n**Evolution Package Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go` - Prompt curation and merging\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go` - Audit logging and snapshot management\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go` - Pipeline orchestration\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go` - Core data structures\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go` - Data collection from runs\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go` - Run classification (bug/feature/etc.)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go` - Lesson extraction\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go` - Script/prompt file generation\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go` - LLM invocation wrapper\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go` - Debouncing and triggering logic\n\n**Ports Interface:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` (contains EvolutionStore and EvolutionEntry)\n\n**Design Documents:**\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`\n\n---\n\n### Data Structures\n\n#### EvolutionResult\n```go\ntype EvolutionResult struct {\n    ID             string   // \"evo-<timestamp>\"\n    ProjectDir     string   // Absolute path to project\n    WorkflowName   string   // Workflow name (e.g., \"develop\")\n    TriggerRunID   string   // Run that triggered evolution\n    Timestamp      string   // RFC3339 format\n    Classification string   // bug/feature/feedback/enhancement/chore\n    Changes        []Change // All modifications made\n    KnowledgeDelta string   // Description of knowledge base updates\n}\n```\n\n#### Change (Evolution Result Record)\n```go\ntype Change struct {\n    Type     string // \"prompt_update\", \"add_step\", \"add_script\"\n    File     string // Relative path to modified file\n    Reason   string // Lesson insight driving the change\n    Snapshot string // Snapshot filename for rollback\n}\n```\n\n#### Lesson (Extracted Knowledge)\n```go\ntype Lesson struct {\n    ID              string   // Unique ID for deduplication\n    Category        string   // \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n    StepType        string   // \"script\" or \"agent\" (for new_step)\n    Target          string   // Target file path (for prompt_improvement)\n    Insight         string   // What pattern was observed\n    SuggestedAction string   // Concrete change to make\n    Evidence        []string // Run IDs supporting the lesson\n    Confidence      string   // \"high\", \"medium\", or \"low\"\n}\n```\n\n#### EvolutionEntry (Database/Storage)\n```go\ntype EvolutionEntry struct {\n    ID             string\n    ProjectDir     string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    TriggerRunID   string\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    Classification string\n    ChangesJSON    string\n    KnowledgeDelta string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Algorithms and Methods\n\n#### 1. Curator.Apply() - Prompt Merging with ACE Principles\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go:32-87`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Reads the target prompt file from disk\n2. Checks if lesson is already present (case-insensitive substring match on insight/action)\n   - If present, returns nil (no change needed)\n3. Takes a snapshot BEFORE modification via `c.Audit.Snapshot()`\n4. Calls LLM with ACE-style system prompt to merge lesson into prompt\n   - System prompt instructs: append to \"## Learned Rules\" section, preserve existing content\n5. Strips markdown code fences from LLM response\n6. Validates response isn't conversational meta-text (checks for patterns like \"I need write permission\", \"Here is the updated\")\n   - If conversational, falls back to appending lesson directly\n7. Writes updated content to target file\n8. Returns Change record with snapshot reference\n\n**Snapshot Protection:** Happens BEFORE file write to capture pre-change state\n\n```go\n// Snapshot before writing\nvar snapName string\nif c.Audit != nil {\n    snapName, _ = c.Audit.Snapshot(lesson.Target)\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. AuditLogger.Snapshot() - Pre-Change File Backup\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:44-73`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Creates `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/` directory if needed\n2. Generates snapshot filename: `<timestamp>-<basename>` (e.g., `20260315T164200-implement.md`)\n3. Opens source file, creates destination in snapshots dir\n4. Copies file content using `io.Copy()`\n5. Returns snapshot filename for audit trail\n\n**Key Detail:** Called with relative paths (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/implement.md`), constructs full path internally\n\n```go\nsnapName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", time.Now().Format(\"20060102T150405\"), basename)\ndstPath := filepath.Join(snapDir, snapName)\n```\n\n#### 3. AuditLogger.Log() - JSONL Audit Trail\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:19-42`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Creates `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` if needed\n2. Opens file in APPEND mode (preserves history)\n3. JSON-marshals EvolutionResult\n4. Appends line to JSONL file (one JSON object per line)\n\n```go\nf, err := os.OpenFile(logPath, os.O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY, 0644)\ndata, err := json.Marshal(result)\nf.Write(append(data, '\\n'))\n```\n\n#### 4. AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() - Knowledge Base Management\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go:124-155`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Reads existing JSONL knowledge base (`.cloche/evolution/knowledge/<workflow>.jsonl`)\n2. Builds index of lesson IDs\n3. For each new lesson:\n   - If ID exists: updates in place (replaces existing entry)\n   - If ID is new: appends to list\n4. If MaxPromptBullets set and exceeded:\n   - Keeps only the newest N lessons (prunes oldest)\n5. Writes merged lessons back to JSONL\n\n```go\n// Merge: update in place if ID exists, append if new\nfor _, l := range lessons {\n    if idx, ok := idIndex[l.ID]; ok {\n        existing[idx] = l // update existing entry\n    } else {\n        existing = append(existing, l)\n    }\n}\n\n// Prune oldest entries if MaxPromptBullets exceeded\nif a.MaxPromptBullets > 0 && len(existing) > a.MaxPromptBullets {\n    existing = existing[len(existing)-a.MaxPromptBullets:]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Pipeline Architecture\n\n**5-Stage Evolution Pipeline:**\n\n1. **Collector** - Gathers data:\n   - Runs since last evolution pass\n   - Knowledge base (JSONL format)\n   - Current prompt files (from `file()` references in workflow)\n   - Current workflow DSL content\n\n2. **Classifier** - Categorizes triggering run via LLM:\n   - Output: \"bug\" | \"feedback\" | \"feature\" | \"enhancement\" | \"chore\"\n   - Used to weight analysis\n\n3. **Reflector** - Extracts lessons via LLM:\n   - Input: collected runs, prompts, workflow, knowledge base\n   - Output: structured lessons with confidence levels\n   - Filters by MinConfidence (high/medium/low)\n   - Deduplicates against knowledge base IDs\n\n4. **Executor Branches** (based on lesson category):\n   - **prompt_improvement** → Curator.Apply()\n   - **new_step** → ScriptGenerator + DSL Mutator\n\n5. **Audit** - Records changes:\n   - Logs to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl`\n   - Creates snapshots in `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`\n   - Updates knowledge base with ID-based deduplication\n\n---\n\n### Snapshot System\n\n**Directory Structure:**\n```\n.cloche/\n  evolution/\n    log.jsonl                     # Append-only JSONL audit trail\n    knowledge/\n      <workflow>.jsonl            # ID-keyed lessons\n    snapshots/\n      20260315T164200-implement.md\n      20260315T164215-develop.cloche\n      ...\n```\n\n**How Snapshots are Used:**\n\n1. **Before Curator writes prompt:**\n   ```go\n   snapName, _ := c.Audit.Snapshot(lesson.Target)  // Returns \"20260315T164200-implement.md\"\n   os.WriteFile(targetPath, []byte(updated), 0644) // Write updated content\n   return &Change{Snapshot: snapName}              // Track for rollback\n   ```\n\n2. **Before workflow file modification:**\n   ```go\n   wfRelPath, _ := filepath.Rel(o.cfg.ProjectDir, data.WorkflowPath)\n   snapName, _ := o.audit.Snapshot(wfRelPath)      // Snapshot before DSL mutation\n   os.WriteFile(data.WorkflowPath, []byte(updated), 0644)\n   ```\n\n3. **Future Rollback** (not yet implemented):\n   - Snapshots enable automated revert via `cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`\n\n---\n\n### Curator Details: Content Guards and Fallbacks\n\n**Guard 1: Lesson Already Present Check** (before LLM call)\n```go\nif lessonAlreadyPresent(string(current), lesson) {\n    return nil, nil  // No change needed\n}\n```\nCase-insensitive substring match on Insight or SuggestedAction.\n\n**Guard 2: Code Fence Stripping**\n```go\nupdated := stripCodeFences(raw)\n```\nExtracts content between ``` markers, removing LLM's commentary/markdown formatting.\n\n**Guard 3: Conversational Response Detection**\n```go\nif isConversationalResponse(updated) {\n    // Fallback: append lesson directly\n    updated = appendLessonDirectly(string(current), lesson)\n}\n```\n\nPatterns detected:\n- \"I need write permission\"\n- \"Could you grant access\"\n- \"Here is the updated prompt:\"\n- \"Let me update...\"\n- Permission-related messages\n- Blocked/access errors\n\nIf detected, fallback to deterministic appending instead of trusting LLM output.\n\n**Fallback Appending:**\n```go\n// If \"## Learned Rules\" section exists, append to it\n// Otherwise, create new section\nif strings.Contains(current, \"## Learned Rules\") {\n    return current + fmt.Sprintf(\"\\n- %s: %s\\n\", lesson.Insight, lesson.SuggestedAction)\n} else {\n    return current + fmt.Sprintf(\"\\n\\n## Learned Rules\\n\\n- %s: %s\\n\", lesson.Insight, lesson.SuggestedAction)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Orchestrator.Run() - Complete Pipeline Execution\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go:51-138`\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n1. Collector.Collect() → CollectedData\n2. Classifier.Classify() → classification string\n3. Reflector.Reflect() → []Lesson (with confidence filtering)\n4. Filter out lessons already in knowledge base (ID deduplication)\n5. Create EvolutionResult\n6. For each lesson:\n   - If category == \"prompt_improvement\":\n     - Call curator.Apply()\n     - Append Change to result\n   - If category == \"new_step\":\n     - Call scriptGen.Generate()\n     - Call mutator to add step/wiring\n     - Append Changes to result\n7. Audit:\n   - audit.UpdateKnowledge() (ID-based merge + prune)\n   - audit.Log(result) (append to JSONL)\n   - evoStore.SaveEvolution() (if available)\n8. Return EvolutionResult\n\n---\n\n### Knowledge Base System\n\n**Format:** JSONL (one JSON Lesson per line)\n\n**Deduplication Strategy:**\n1. Lessons keyed by ID field\n2. If same ID appears: update in place (not append)\n3. ReadKnowledge parses JSONL, builds ID index\n4. WriteKnowledge serializes back\n\n**Deduplication Layers:**\n1. **Orchestrator layer** (before Curator/ScriptGen):\n   ```go\n   if data.KnowledgeBase != \"\" {\n       var fresh []Lesson\n       for _, l := range lessons {\n           if l.ID != \"\" && strings.Contains(data.KnowledgeBase, l.ID) {\n               continue  // Skip already-seen ID\n           }\n           fresh = append(fresh, l)\n       }\n       lessons = fresh\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **AuditLogger layer** (UpdateKnowledge):\n   ```go\n   for _, l := range lessons {\n       if idx, ok := idIndex[l.ID]; ok {\n           existing[idx] = l  // Update in place\n       } else {\n           existing = append(existing, l)\n       }\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Pruning:**\n```go\nif a.MaxPromptBullets > 0 && len(existing) > a.MaxPromptBullets {\n    existing = existing[len(existing)-a.MaxPromptBullets:]  // Keep newest N\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration with Rest of System\n\n**Ports Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`):\n```go\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**Trigger System** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`):\n- Debounces evolution runs per project+workflow\n- Resets timer if new run completes within debounce window\n- Default: 30 seconds\n\n**LLM Client** (`/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`):\n- Interface: `Complete(ctx, systemPrompt, userPrompt) (string, error)`\n- CommandLLMClient: invokes external command (e.g., Claude Code CLI)\n- Passes system prompt via `--system-prompt` flag\n- Uses `-p` (print mode) for non-interactive output\n\n---\n\n### Testing Strategy\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` (1198 lines)\n  - Collector tests\n  - Classifier tests\n  - Reflector tests\n  - Audit Logger tests (Log, Snapshot, UpdateKnowledge, deduplication, pruning)\n  - Curator tests (prompt update, code fence stripping, conversational response detection)\n  - ScriptGenerator tests\n  - Utility function tests\n\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go`\n  - Error handling and edge cases\n  - Mock stores for integration testing\n\n- `/workspace/test/integration/evolution_test.go`\n  - End-to-end pipeline test\n\n**Mock Implementations:**\n- `fakeLLM` - Returns fixed responses\n- `callTrackingLLM` - Records all LLM calls (system/user prompts)\n- `errLLM` - Returns errors\n- `mockEvolutionStore` - Tracks saves/queries\n- `mockCaptureStore` - Returns test captures\n\n---\n\n### File Structure on Disk\n\n**Evolution artifacts location:**\n```\n<project-root>/\n  .cloche/\n    evolution/\n      log.jsonl                      # Append-only audit trail\n      knowledge/\n        develop.jsonl               # Knowledge base for 'develop' workflow\n        test.jsonl                  # Knowledge base for 'test' workflow\n      snapshots/\n        20260315T150405-implement.md\n        20260315T150420-develop.cloche\n        ...\n    develop.cloche                  # Workflow DSL (can be modified)\n    prompts/\n      implement.md                  # Prompt files (can be modified)\n      fix.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Principles\n\n1. **Snapshot-First**: Snapshots taken before ANY file write (Curator or Mutator)\n2. **Deduplication**: Multi-layer (Orchestrator + AuditLogger) prevents lesson re-processing\n3. **LLM Validation**: Multiple guards against LLM producing meta-conversation instead of content\n4. **Deterministic Fallback**: If LLM fails validation, append lesson directly without re-calling\n5. **Audit Trail**: Complete JSONL history of every evolution pass with reasons\n6. **Project Scoping**: All evolution state scoped by `project_dir + workflow_name`\n7. **ACE Principles**: Prompts treated as structured playbooks with accumulated lessons, not monoliths\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Key Method |\n|-----------|---|---|\n| **Curator** | Merge lessons into prompts | `Apply(ctx, projectDir, lesson)` → Change |\n| **AuditLogger** | Log changes + snapshots + knowledge | `Log()`, `Snapshot()`, `UpdateKnowledge()` |\n| **Orchestrator** | Wire all stages together | `Run(ctx, triggerRunID, stores)` → EvolutionResult |\n| **Collector** | Gather input data | `Collect(ctx, stores)` → CollectedData |\n| **Classifier** | Categorize run | `Classify(ctx, prompt)` → string |\n| **Reflector** | Extract lessons | `Reflect(ctx, data, classification)` → []Lesson |\n| **ScriptGenerator** | Generate validation scripts | `Generate(ctx, projectDir, lesson)` → GeneratedScript |\n| **Trigger** | Debounce pipeline runs | `Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID)` |\n\n---\n\nAll source files are in `/workspace/internal/evolution/` and thoroughly tested in `evolution_test.go` and `corruption_test.go`."}],"totalDurationMs":95229,"totalTokens":57807,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1411,"cache_read_input_tokens":51790,"output_tokens":4602,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_